--
-- Data for Name: precaution; Type: TABLE DATA; Schema: public; Owner: postgres
--

COPY public.precaution (precaution_id, precaution_text) FROM stdin;
9	Istirahat cukup, Minum banyak cairan (air putih, jus), Konsumsi makanan bergizi, Obat pereda nyeri bebas jika diperlukan untuk sakit kepala
10	Meningkatkan asupan cairan, terutama air putih, Hindari minuman berkafein atau alkohol yang dapat memperburuk dehidrasi, Konsumsi buah dan sayuran kaya air
11	Cukup tidur (7-9 jam per malam), Manajemen stres (misalnya meditasi, hobi), Pola makan teratur dan seimbang, Melakukan aktivitas fisik ringan secara teratur
12	Increase fluid intake, especially water throughout the day.;Avoid excessive caffeine and alcohol, which can contribute to dehydration.
13	Use a humidifier in your living or sleeping area, especially if indoors in dry, cold weather.;Stay hydrated and avoid prolonged exposure to very cold, dry air if possible.
14	Rest adequately and ensure good hydration.;Gargle with warm salt water to soothe the throat.
15	Consult a doctor if you suspect sleep apnea (e.g., loud snoring, daytime fatigue).;Try sleeping on your side to reduce snoring and mouth breathing.
16	Avoid large meals close to bedtime and identify trigger foods (e.g., spicy, fatty, acidic foods).;Elevate the head of your bed when sleeping.
17	Get plenty of rest.;Drink plenty of fluids (water, herbal tea, broth).;Gargle with warm salt water to relieve sore throat.;Consider over-the-counter pain relievers/fever reducers (e.g., paracetamol).;Wash hands frequently to prevent spreading.
18	Rest your voice.;Drink warm liquids (e.g., tea with honey).;Gargle with warm salt water.;Use throat lozenges or hard candies to soothe the throat.;Avoid irritants like smoke and polluted air.
19	Get plenty of rest.;Stay well-hydrated by drinking fluids.;Use over-the-counter medications for fever and body aches.;Avoid close contact with others to prevent transmission.;Consult a doctor if symptoms worsen or don't improve, especially for specific antiviral treatments.
20	Segera konsultasi ke dokter untuk pemeriksaan dan tes darah (NS1, trombosit).;Perbanyak asupan cairan (air putih, jus buah, oralit) untuk mencegah dehidrasi.;Istirahat total dan pantau tanda-tanda bahaya seperti pendarahan atau nyeri perut hebat.
21	Periksakan diri ke dokter karena pengobatan memerlukan antibiotik.;Jaga kebersihan makanan dan minuman yang dikonsumsi.;Istirahat yang cukup dan konsumsi makanan lunak yang mudah dicerna.
22	Beristirahat yang cukup dan perbanyak minum air hangat.;Konsumsi obat pereda demam dan nyeri yang dijual bebas, seperti paracetamol.;Gunakan masker dan hindari kontak dekat dengan orang lain untuk mencegah penularan.
23	Get plenty of rest to help your body recover.;Stay hydrated by drinking water, juice, or warm soup.;Use over-the-counter decongestants or pain relievers if needed.;Wash hands frequently to prevent spreading the virus.
24	Identify and avoid your specific allergy triggers.;Keep your home clean and use an air purifier if possible.;Consider using over-the-counter antihistamines.;Rinse your nasal passages with a saline solution.
25	Rest is crucial for recovery.;Drink plenty of fluids to prevent dehydration.;Monitor for fever or worsening symptoms and consult a doctor if they occur.;Consider an annual flu vaccine for future prevention.
26	Use a saline nasal spray to keep nasal passages moist.;Apply a warm, moist washcloth to your face several times a day.;Inhale steam from a bowl of hot water or a shower.;Consult a doctor if you experience severe headache, facial pain, or a fever.
27	Allow yourself time to grieve and process your feelings without judgment.;Talk about your feelings with trusted friends, family, or a counselor.;Maintain a regular routine for sleep, meals, and daily activities.;Engage in hobbies and physical activities you enjoy to help improve your mood.
28	If feelings of sadness are severe, last for more than two weeks, and interfere with daily life, it is crucial to seek professional help.;Avoid isolation; try to stay connected with a supportive social network.;Incorporate regular exercise, as it has been shown to alleviate symptoms of depression.;Avoid making major life decisions while feeling deeply distressed.
29	Practice relaxation techniques such as deep breathing, mindfulness, or meditation.;Limit caffeine and other stimulants that can increase feelings of anxiety.;Write down your thoughts and feelings in a journal to help process them.;Consult a healthcare professional if anxiety is persistent and difficult to control.
30	Consult a healthcare provider for a comprehensive health screening.;Focus on achieving a healthy weight through a balanced diet and regular exercise.;Incorporate more whole grains, fruits, and vegetables into your diet while reducing processed foods and sugar.
31	Get a blood sugar test (like A1c) to check for prediabetes or diabetes.;Limit intake of sugary beverages and refined carbohydrates.;Engage in at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic activity per week.
32	Monitor your blood pressure regularly at home or at a pharmacy.;Reduce your sodium (salt) intake by avoiding processed and packaged foods.;Incorporate stress-management techniques like meditation or deep breathing exercises.
33	Weight loss is the most effective way to manage or reverse NAFLD.;Avoid high-fructose corn syrup and other added sugars.;Follow a diet rich in antioxidants, such as the Mediterranean diet, and limit saturated fats.
\.


